==English==
===Etymology===
OE. aournen, anournen, adornen, OF. aorner, fr. L. aaornare; ad + ornare to furnish, embellish.  See [[Adore]], [[Ornate]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈdoɹn/
*{{audio|en-us-adorn.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
#Make more beautiful and attractive; to [[decorate]].
#:a lady was  adorned with jewels
#:a man adorned with noble statuary and  columns
#:a character adorned with every Christian grace
#:a gallery of paintings was adorned with the works of some of the  great masters

